*Expected Behavior*

`docker compose up` should automatically update npm packages when `package.json` is modified.

*Current Behavior*

Node.js app raises `Module not found` error with new packages

*Possible Solution*

Explained in detail in <https://www.notion.so/osam-handover/00807e3b037e43d1bcff54d2c6b591f1#678622aff4e24f59ad78b0ea62639bcb|Notion>

> Run `docker exec -it container_name npm install`

*Steps to Reproduce*

1. Add new package in `package.json`
2. Run `docker compose up` or `npm run dev`

*Possible Implementation*

Fix `Dockerfile` and volume configurations in `docker-compose.yml` to cache and update `node_modules` correctly.
